# ECS Rules

## Architecture

Bevy-inspired ECS: `World` ‚Üí `Entity` ‚Üí `Component`, with `System` functions that query components.

```
ecs/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ entity.rs          # Entity type (index + generation), EntityAllocator
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ component.rs       # Component trait, ComponentId, ComponentInfo
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ sparse_set.rs      # SparseSet<T> ‚Äî O(1) storage with dense iteration
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ archetype.rs       # Archetype, ArchetypeGraph ‚Äî entity grouping
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ storage.rs         # AnyComponentStorage, ComponentStorage traits
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ world.rs           # World ‚Äî central ECS container, EntityWorldMut builder
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ query/             # Query<T>, type-safe component queries
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ resource.rs        # Res<T>, ResMut<T>, Resources container
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ schedule.rs        # CoreStage, SystemStage, Stage ordering
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ system/            # System trait, function systems, SystemParam
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ systems/           # Built-in systems (transform propagation, sprite rendering)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/        # Built-in components (transform, sprite, hierarchy, etc.)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ collision.rs       # Collision detection algorithms
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ broad_phase.rs     # SpatialHash broad-phase
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ physics_world.rs   # PhysicsWorld integration
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ input_manager.rs   # InputManager, InputBinding
```

## Component Rules

- Components MUST be plain data ‚Äî no methods with side effects
- Derive `Debug` and `Clone` on all components
- Component storage uses `SparseSet<T>` for O(1) insert/remove/get
- FFI exports for components go in `ffi/component_*.rs` files

## Entity Rules

- Entities are lightweight identifiers: index + generation
- Created via `EntityAllocator` or `World::spawn()`
- `EntityWorldMut` provides a builder pattern for spawning with components
- NEVER store entity IDs as raw integers ‚Äî always use the `Entity` type

## Query Rules

- Use `Query<T>` for type-safe component access
- Queries iterate only entities that have the requested components
- `QueryIter` / `QueryIterMut` for immutable/mutable iteration
- Never access `SparseSet` internals directly from systems

## System Rules

- Systems implement `System` trait (`name()` + `run(&mut self, &mut World)`)
- Function systems convert closures into systems via `SystemParam`
- Schedule systems into `CoreStage` stages (First, PreUpdate, Update, PostUpdate, Last)
- Built-in: `TransformPropagationSystem`, `SpriteRenderSystem`

## Hierarchy and Transforms

- `Hierarchy` component for parent/child relationships
- `Transform2D` ‚Äî local transform, `GlobalTransform2D` ‚Äî world transform
- `TransformPropagationSystem` computes global transforms from hierarchy
- Propagation runs automatically in the `PostUpdate` stage

## Physics Integration

- `Collider`, `RigidBody` components for physics
- `SpatialHash` broad-phase for collision culling
- Collision algorithms: AABB, circle, OBB, mixed
- `PhysicsWorld` integrates collision detection with ECS
